{
  "description": {
    "title": "K-ETS structural hoarding on the banking equilibrium (small, fast)",
    "paper": "PLANiT K-MSR working paper (July 2026), Sections 3-4: compliance entities bank against future tightening without pricing the carry (registry banked-to-certified ratio rising 0.03 -> 0.17); repo mechanism docs in solvers/banking.py module docstring.",
    "mechanism": "hoarding_inflow h_t [Mt] is withdrawn from the year's circulating supply (raising that year's static price), accumulates in the aggregate bank, and re-enters the window budget when the drawdown window opens. Hoarding years are static-regime years BY DEFINITION: the banking window never starts at or before a year with h_t > 0. Requires model_approach = banking; banking_strict_no_arbitrage = false (R20: hoarding is the documented lambda ~ 0 no-arbitrage violation).",
    "inputs": "Cap 100 -> 80 Mt over 2026-2030 (KRW prices), 2 linear-MAC participants (BAU 110 -> 98 Mt), no free allocation, r = 5.5%; hoarding scenario withdraws 8 Mt in 2026 and 6 Mt in 2027.",
    "expected_output": {
      "no hoarding (2026-2030)": [
        6670.25,
        7037.11,
        7424.16,
        7832.48,
        8263.27
      ],
      "hoarding (2026-2030)": [
        9572.73,
        9572.73,
        5707.6,
        6021.52,
        6352.7
      ],
      "reading": "Without hoarding the whole horizon is one banking window: a pure Hotelling ramp at exactly (1+r) = 1.055 per year. With hoarding, 2026-27 are static years at an ELEVATED price (the shortage-plus-hoard 18 Mt clears against the residual MAC in both years), and the window opens in 2028 with the 14 Mt hoard re-entering the budget - prices DROP by ~40% and then ramp at 5.5%/yr again. The hoard shifts scarcity from the future into the present and back."
    },
    "run": "PYTHONPATH=src .venv/bin/python -m ets.cli --config examples/k_ets_hoarding_basic.json"
  },
